The paper deals with the efficient processing of $k$-nearest neighbor queries, which is a common problem in spatial databases and location-based applications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions classification in data mining, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of the MapReduce framework suggests that the paper may also belong to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
